        -:    5:/*
        -:    6: * uring.c — batch operation execution with optional io_uring acceleration.
        -:    7: *
        -:    8: * When io_uring is available (g_uring_available == 1) we attempt to submit
        -:    9: * all operations as a single SQE batch, falling back to sequential execution
        -:   10: * if setup fails or the operations are not independent.
        -:   11: *
        -:   12: * For operations that are not natively expressible as io_uring SQEs (e.g.
        -:   13: * mkdir, chmod) we fall through to the sequential fallback.  The io_uring
        -:   14: * path currently accelerates only BATCH_RM_FILE (via IORING_OP_UNLINKAT)
        -:   15: * and BATCH_TOUCH (via IORING_OP_STATX to probe + separate utimensat).
        -:   16: *
        -:   17: * The implementation uses raw syscalls (SYS_io_uring_setup / _enter /
        -:   18: * _register) and shared-memory mapped rings to avoid any dependency on
        -:   19: * liburing.
        -:   20: *
        -:   21: * Correctness guarantee: if io_uring is unavailable, or if any part of the
        -:   22: * ring setup fails, we fall back to fallback_exec_seq() which is always
        -:   23: * correct.
        -:   24: */
